"**Event Summary: #putinmissing**\n\nSocial media activity regarding the hashtag #putinmissing consists primarily of unverified claims and speculative commentary rather than confirmed factual reports.\n\n*   **Official Claims:** One post cites an \"official confirmation\" of a \"distinct detail 13\" associated with file number 213, though the source is labeled unverified. Another post references a \"security briefing\" and a \"private police bulletin\" containing a disputed timestamp of 73:15.\n*   **Visual Evidence:** Two posts include links to images or videos. One claims to show Putin (\"There he is!!\"), while another points to an alleged anomaly on top of the Kremlin (\"Look what is missing from the top of the #Kremlin today\").\n*   **Speculation:** One post suggests the situation is a preparation for St. Patrick's Day, linking the hashtag to #putindead.\n\n**Disputed/Unverified Information:**\n*   The existence and content of \"detail 13\" and file number 213 are unverified.\n*   The \"73:15 timestamp\" is explicitly described as disputed.\n*   The visual evidence provided in the linked media is unverified and contradicts the premise of the hashtag in at least one instance (claiming Putin is present).\n*   The connection to St. Patrick's Day is speculative humor.\n\n**Credibility Note:** All retrieved posts are from unverified users with low engagement (0–11 reactions). There is no consensus on factual details; claims range from official-sounding but unverified bulletins to visual hoaxes and jokes. No concrete evidence supports the core premise of Putin being missing."